COMMON.text:
MACRO
         COMMON  &TYPE=X
         AIF  ('&TYPE' EQ 'CSECT').CSECT
VZAPCOMM DSECT
         AGO  .COMM
.CSECT   ANOP
VZAPCOMM CSECT
VZAPCOMM AMODE 31
VZAPCOMM RMODE ANY
         USING VZAPCOMM,R12
.COMM    ANOP
* ------------------------------------------------------------------- *
*                                                                     *
*         Internal trace                                              *
*                                                                     *
* ------------------------------------------------------------------- *
TRACE000 DS    0H
DXD      USING DXD_PREFIX,R13
         STM   R0,R15,COMM_TRACE_SAVE
         L     R2,COMM_TRACE_CURR
         C     R2,COMM_TRACE_LAST
         BNE   TRACE010
         L     R2,COMM_TRACE_1ST
         B     TRACE020
TRACE010 DS    0H
         LA    R2,TR_ENTRY_L(R2)
TRACE020 DS    0H
         ST    R2,COMM_TRACE_CURR
         USING TR_ENTRY,R2
         MVC   TR_CSECT,DXD.DXD_CSECT
         MVC   TR_ID,0(R14)
         MVC   TR_DATA1,COMM_TRACE_ITEM_1
         MVC   TR_DATA2,COMM_TRACE_ITEM_2
         XC    COMM_TRACE_ITEM_1,COMM_TRACE_ITEM_1
         XC    COMM_TRACE_ITEM_2,COMM_TRACE_ITEM_2
         ICM   R3,15,COMM_TRACE_TPUT
         BZ    TRACE030
         MVC   0(TR_ENTRY_L,R3),TR_ENTRY
         TPUT  (R3),TR_ENTRY_L
TRACE030 DS    0H
         LM    R0,R15,COMM_TRACE_SAVE
         B     8(R14)
         DROP  DXD

COMM_TRACE_SAVE        DS    16F

COMM_TRACE             DC    A(0)
                       DC    C'1STX'
COMM_TRACE_1ST         DC    A(0)
                       DC    C'LAST'
COMM_TRACE_LAST        DC    A(0)
                       DC    C'CURR'
COMM_TRACE_CURR        DC    A(0)

                       DC    CL4'TPUT'
COMM_TRACE_TPUT        DC    A(0)

ITRACE.text:
.* ------------------------------------------------------------------*
.*                                                                   *
.*                        TRACE MACRO                                *
.*                                                                   *
.*       The trace function always captures the last three bytes of  *
.*       the active task's TCB address and bytes 3-7 of the active   *
.*       CSECT's name, and a trace ID.                               *
.*                                                                   *
.*       One or two data elements (8 bytes each) may be captured at  *
.*       any trace point.  The data to be captured may be specified  *
.*       in either of two ways: DATA1 or RDATA1 and DATA2 or RDATA2. *
.*       DATA1 and RDATA1 are mutually exclusive as are DATA2 and    *
.*       RDATA2.  DATA1 and DATA2 specify the address of data to be  *
.*       captured, RDATA1 and RDATA2 specify a register whose        *
.*       contents are to be captured.                                *
.*                                                                   *
.*       For example:                                                *
.*                                                                   *
.*                 ITRACE ID=POINTA,DATA1=VALUE1,RDATA2=R4           *
.*                                                                   *
.*          In this case the trace entry would include the TCB       *
.*          address, CSECT name, ID "POINTA", 8 bytes of data        *
.*          beginning at value1's address and the contents of        *
.*          register 4.                                              *
.*                                                                   *
.* ------------------------------------------------------------------*
         MACRO
&NAME    ITRACE &X,&ID=,&DATA1=,&DATA2=,&RDATA1=,&RDATA2=
         LCLA  &L
         AIF   (T'&X NE 'O').ERR0030
         AIF   (T'&DATA1 NE 'O' AND T'&RDATA1 NE 'O').ERR0010
         AIF   (T'&DATA2 NE 'O' AND T'&RDATA2 NE 'O').ERR0020
         AIF   ('&SYSPARM' EQ 'NOTRACE').MEXIT
         AIF   (T'&DATA1 EQ 'O').DATA030
         AIF   ('&DATA1'(1,1) EQ '(').DATA010
         LA    R14,&DATA1                   DATA ADDRESS
         MVC   COMM_TRACE_ITEM_1,0(R14)     MOVE DATA
         AGO   .DATA040
.DATA010 ANOP
         AIF   (N'&DATA1 EQ 1).DATA020
&L       SETA  &DATA1(2)
         AIF   (&L GT 8).ERR0040
         MVC   COMM_TRACE_ITEM_1(&L),&DATA1(1)
         AGO   .DATA040
.DATA020 ANOP
         MVC   COMM_TRACE_ITEM_1,0&DATA1    MOVE DATA
         AGO   .DATA040
.DATA030 ANOP
         AIF   (T'&RDATA1 EQ 'O').DATA040
         STCM  &RDATA1,15,COMM_TRACE_ITEM_1 SAVE REGISTER CONTENTS
.DATA040 ANOP
         AIF   (T'&DATA2 EQ 'O').DATA070
         AIF   ('&DATA2'(1,1) EQ '(').DATA050
         LA    R14,&DATA2                   DATA ADDRESS
         MVC   COMM_TRACE_ITEM_2,0(R14)     MOVE DATA
         AGO   .DATA080
.DATA050 ANOP
         AIF   (N'&DATA2 EQ 1).DATA060
&L       SETA  &DATA2(2)
         AIF   (&L GT 8).ERR0050
         MVC   COMM_TRACE_ITEM_2(&L),&DATA2(1)
         AGO   .DATA080
.DATA060 ANOP
         MVC   COMM_TRACE_ITEM_2,0&DATA2    MOVE DATA
         AGO   .DATA080
.DATA070 ANOP
         AIF   (T'&RDATA2 EQ 'O').DATA080
         STCM  &RDATA2,15,COMM_TRACE_ITEM_2 SAVE REGISTER CONTENTS
.DATA080 ANOP
         BAL   R14,TRACE000                 ENTER TRACE ROUTINE
         AIF      (T'&ID EQ 'O').NOID
&NAME    DC    CL8'&ID'                     TRACE ID
         AGO   .ID
.NOID    ANOP
&NAME    DC    CL8'**NOID**'
.ID      ANOP
         MEXIT
.ERR0010 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'DATA1 AND RDATA1 ARE MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE'
         MEXIT
.ERR0020 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'DATA2 AND RDATA2 ARE MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE'
         MEXIT
.ERR0030 ANOP
         MNOTE 4,'POSITIONAL PARM FOUND'
         MEXIT
.ERR0040 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'LENGTH FOR ITEM 1 MUST BE 8 OR LESS'
         MEXIT
.ERR0050 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'LENGTH FOR ITEM 2 MUST BE 8 OR LESS'
.MEXIT   ANOP
         MEXIT
         MEND

* ------------------------------------------------------------------- *

$VNEVER     EQU   X'40'                 .. NEVER VDEFINE
$VGET       EQU   X'20'                 .. VGET WHEN VDEFINED
$VPUT       EQU   X'10'                 .. VPUT BEFORE VDELETE

VDEF.text:
MACRO
         VDEF  &BASE=,               BASE ADDRESS OF VARIABLES AREA    +
               &NAME=,               NAME DEFINED TO SPF               +
               &DATA=,               DATA ADDRESS                      +
               &LENGTH=,             DATA LENGTH                       +
               &FORM=,               DATA FORMAT                       +
               &FLAGS=00
         GBLC  &VBASE
         AIF   (T'&BASE EQ 'O').LBL0010
&VBASE   SETC  '&BASE'
         MEXIT
.LBL0010 ANOP
         AIF   (T'&NAME EQ 'O').ERR0010
         AIF   (T'&LENGTH  EQ 'O').ERR0020
         AIF   (T'&FORM    EQ 'O').ERR0030
         AIF   ('&VBASE' EQ '').ERR0060
         DC    CL8'&NAME'             NAME KNOWN TO SPF
         DC    AL1(&FLAGS)            FLAGS/INDICATORS
         DC    AL4(&LENGTH)           LENGTH
         DC    CL8'&FORM'             VARIABLE FORMAT
         DC    AL2(&DATA-&VBASE)      DISPLACEMENT TO DATA
         MEXIT
.ERR0010 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'NAME IS A REQUIRED PARAMETER'
         MEXIT
.ERR0020 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'LENGTH IS A REQUIRED PARAMETER'
         MEXIT
.ERR0030 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'FORM IS A REQUIRED PARAMETER'
         MEXIT
.ERR0040 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'VARIABLE NAME IS DUPLICATED'
         MEXIT
.ERR0060 ANOP
         MNOTE 12,'BASE MUST BE DEFINED BEFORE VARIABLES CAN BE DEFINED+
               '
         MEND
